From: NextOS-Elite-Edition <noreply@nextos>
Subject: [PATCH] Recognize NextOS-Elite-Edition as EmuELEC fork

NextOS-Retro-Elite-Edition is a downstream fork of EmuELEC targeting
Amlogic-old TV boxes (S905X/W with Mali-450, kernel 3.14). It ships the
same /etc/os-release schema as EmuELEC (COREELEC_DEVICE, COREELEC_PROJECT,
LIBREELEC_*) but reports NAME="NextOS-Retro-Elite-Edition".

Without recognition PortMaster falls through to PlatformBase, losing
gamelist_add(), GCD_PortMaster compat helpers, and the EmuELEC bash
detection branch. Ports install but never appear in EmulationStation.

Two-line fix:
- hardware.py: alias info['name'] to 'EmuELEC' when it starts with
  'NextOS' (matches EmuELEC behavior including device='Amlogic-old' from
  COREELEC_DEVICE in os-release).
- platform.py: add 'nextos' explicit alias in HM_PLATFORMS dict pointing
  to PlatformEmuELEC, so name='nextos' (via .CUSTOM_DEVICE for users
  setting it directly) also resolves correctly.

Tested on NextOS-Retro-Elite-Edition 4.8.2 / Amlogic-old / S905W: ports
download → gamelist.xml entries created → ES sees ports immediately.

Signed-off-by: Felipe felc18-blip <fel.c18@gmail.com>
---
 PortMaster/pylibs/harbourmaster/hardware.py | 5 +++++
 PortMaster/pylibs/harbourmaster/platform.py | 1 +
 2 files changed, 6 insertions(+)

diff --git a/PortMaster/pylibs/harbourmaster/hardware.py b/PortMaster/pylibs/harbourmaster/hardware.py
--- a/PortMaster/pylibs/harbourmaster/hardware.py
+++ b/PortMaster/pylibs/harbourmaster/hardware.py
@@ -X,Y +X,Y @@ def new_device_info():
     info['device'] = info['device'].lower().replace(' ', '-')
 
+    # NextOS-Elite-Edition is an EmuELEC fork — alias name so PortMaster
+    # picks PlatformEmuELEC (gamelist_add, GCD_PortMaster, etc.).
+    if info.get('name', '').lower().startswith('nextos'):
+        info['name'] = 'EmuELEC'
+
     info.setdefault('name', 'Unknown')
     info.setdefault('version', '0.0.0')

diff --git a/PortMaster/pylibs/harbourmaster/platform.py b/PortMaster/pylibs/harbourmaster/platform.py
--- a/PortMaster/pylibs/harbourmaster/platform.py
+++ b/PortMaster/pylibs/harbourmaster/platform.py
@@ -X,Y +X,Y @@ HM_PLATFORMS = {
     'emuelec':   PlatformEmuELEC,
+    'nextos':    PlatformEmuELEC,  # NextOS-Elite-Edition fork
     'unofficialos': PlatformUOS,
